<h3 id=3D"SD:InternationalPaymentOutward(Channels)-Referencedataconsumption=
"><strong><span data-teams=3D"true">Reference data consumption</span></stro=
ng></h3>
<h4 id=3D"SD:InternationalPaymentOutward(Channels)-DataFlowSummary">Data Fl=
ow Summary</h4>
<p>Data will be transferred from <strong>GPP</strong> to <strong>Sterling</=
strong> via a scheduled batch job running at a predefined interval (to be c=
onfirmed by the Product Owner and agreed with the Sterling team).</p>
<p>Once received, the data will be transformed by<strong> EBIP</strong>, fo=
llowing the same transformation logic currently used for <strong>WLive</str=
ong>.</p>
<p>The transformed data will then be persisted in<strong> COSMIC</strong> t=
hrough a newly created <strong>Mesh Maintenance API</strong> (API name to b=
e confirmed and implementation required).</p>
<h4 id=3D"SD:InternationalPaymentOutward(Channels)-ProposedMeshMaintenanceA=
PIEndpoints">Proposed Mesh Maintenance API Endpoints</h4>
<p>The following endpoints are proposed to support data persistence: (It's =
assumed that the new file will replace all data in the existing table)</p>
<ul>
<li>Insert Bank List</li>
<li>Insert Country List</li>
<li>Insert Currency List</li>
<li>Insert NCC Rules</li>
<li>Insert Countries per Currency</li>
<li>Insert Purpose of Payment Code / Description <strong><span style=3D"col=
or: rgb(255,0,0);">(TBC)</span></strong></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p>Below is the context diagram illustrating how data is flowing from GPP t=
o COSMIC:&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong><span data-teams=3D"true"> <map id=3D"gliffy-map-2310061089-4613=
" name=3D"gliffy-map-2310061089-4613"></map> </span></strong></p>
<table width=3D"100%" class=3D"gliffy-macro-table">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<table class=3D"gliffy-macro-inner-table">
<caption align=3D"bottom">
