<h4 id=3D"SD:InternationalPaymentOutward(Channels)-EXPAPIEndpointsforrefere=
ncedata:"><span data-teams=3D"true">EXP API Endpoints for reference data:</=
span></h4>
<p><span data-teams=3D"true">The following EXP API will be implemented to r=
etrieve list of reference data:</span></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col>
<col>
<col>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">MFE&nbsp;</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">API Name</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Input</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Output</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Note</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Payment / Beneficiary</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">GET /bankDetailList</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Swift / BIC</li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Bank name</p><p>Bank City, Bank Country</p><p=
>Bank identifier</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>This API is for UI to retrieves a list of Ide=
ntifier and bank detail with a partial value of SWIFT/BIC they have inputte=
d.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Payment / Beneficiary</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">GET /countryList</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">N/A</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>list of</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Country codes</li>
<li>Country names</li>
<li>Scenario Index</li>
<li>NCC prefix / type <strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">(TBC)</s=
pan></strong></li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Filter and only return the list of Countries =
that is currently supported by W1T&nbsp;</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>This API is for UI to retrieves a list of countries for user to select =
when making international payment or create international beneficiary.</li>
<li>It also returns a list of scenario index for the Front end to determine=
 which combination of fields to be displayed a particular country.&nbsp;</l=
i>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Payment / Beneficiary</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">GET /currencyList</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Country code</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">list of Currency codes and Currency names</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Filter and only return the list of Currencies=
 that is currently supported by W1T&nbsp;</p><p>This API is for UI to retri=
eves a list of currencies supported for the selected country, for user to s=
elect when making international payment or create international beneficiary=
.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Payment / Beneficiary</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">GET /bankDetailListByNCC</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>Country code / NCC type</li>
<li>Branch identifier (e.g. ABA / CNAPS)</li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Bank name<p>Bank City, Bank Country</p><p>Bank i=
dentifier</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Search bank detail by specific identifier for=
 countries</p><p>This API is for UI to retrieves a list of Identifier and b=
ank detail with a partial value of Identifier they have inputted.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Payment</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">GET /cutoffList</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Country code</li>
<li>Currency code</li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Cut-off time</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Provide the earliest cut-off time for currenc=
y / country to show to the users as warning.&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Payment&nbsp;</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">GET /purposeCodeList</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>Country code</li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>List of</p>
<ul>
<li>purpose code</li>
<li>purpose of payment description</li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Return the list of purpose code for display in t=
he Reason of payment dropdown.&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><s>Payment / Beneficiary</s></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><s>GET /nccList</s></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li><s>Country code&nbsp;</s></li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><s>List of</s></p>
<ul>
<li><s>Ncc type&nbsp;</s></li>
<li><s>Ncc description&nbsp;</s></li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><s>Return the list of supported branches iden=
tifier / NCC to the UI.</s></p><p><s>The list of NCC type will need to be p=
assed on to GET /bankDetailList for searching the Identifier and bank detai=
l.</s></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Payment / Beneficiary</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Payment / Beneficiary</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Payment / Beneficiary</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Payment / Beneficiary</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Payment / Beneficiary</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h5 id=3D"SD:InternationalPaymentOutward(Channels)-SampleEXPAPIdesign:"><sp=
an>Sample EXP API design:</span></h5>
<div id=3D"expander-756234896" class=3D"expand-container">
<div role=3D"heading" aria-level=3D"6" id=3D"expander-control-756234896" cl=
ass=3D"expand-control"><button type=3D"button" id=3D"expand-button-75623489=
6" class=3D"aui-button aui-button-link aui-button-link-icon-text" aria-expa=
nded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"expander-content-756234896"><span class=3D"e=
xpand-icon aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-chevron-down" aria-hidden=
=3D"true"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text conf-macro-render">Exam=
ple swagger</span></button>
</div>
<div role=3D"region" id=3D"expander-content-756234896" class=3D"expand-cont=
ent" aria-labelledby=3D"expand-button-756234896">
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Reference data</b><span class=3D"collapse-source ex=
pand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-icon ic=
on">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</span></=
span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: yaml; gutter: false; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Con=
fluence">openapi: 3.0.3
info:
  version: 1.0.0
  title: Galaxy-Payment Reference Data Experience API
  description: &gt;-
    This API provides reference data endpoints for the Galaxy SPA to suppor=
t
    international payment and beneficiary creation flows. It allows retriev=
ing
    bank details, country lists, currency lists, cut-off times, and purpose
    codes.
  contact:
    url: https://mesh.westpac.com.au/components/microFrontends/galaxy-payme=
nt
  x-baseSchemaVersion: 0.8.0
servers:
  - url: /exp/galaxy/payment/v2
paths:
  /bankDetailList:
    get:
      tags:
        - ReferenceData
      description: &gt;-
        Retrieves a list of bank details (SWIFT/BIC code, bank name, bank
        location, country) matching a partial SWIFT/BIC value inputted by t=
he
        user. Used during international payment initiation or beneficiary
        creation to look up bank details by SWIFT/BIC code. Data is sourced=
 from
        the bank_list table filtered by SWIFT/BIC records (where ncc_type i=
s
        null or empty).
      operationId: getBankDetailList
      parameters:
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-authorization'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-brandId'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-channelType'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-deviceExperience'
        - name: search
          in: query
          description: &gt;-
            Partial SWIFT/BIC code to search for. Minimum 2 characters. The=
 API
            will return all banks whose SWIFT/BIC code starts with or conta=
ins
            this value.
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
            minLength: 2
            maxLength: 11
            pattern: ^[A-Za-z0-9]+$
          example: CHAS
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/pageSize'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/pageKey'
      responses:
        '200':
          description: A list of bank details matching the SWIFT/BIC search=
 criteria
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
                properties:
                  entities:
                    type: object
                    properties:
                      bankDetails:
                        type: array
                        items:
                          type: object
                          description: &gt;-
                            Bank detail record from bank_list table (SWIFT/=
BIC
                            entries)
                          required:
                            - id
                            - bankCode
                            - countryCode
                          properties:
                            id:
                              description: Unique identifier for this bank =
detail record
                              type: string
                              pattern: &gt;-
                                ^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-5][0-9a-f]{3}-[=
089ab][0-9a-f]{3}-[0-9a-f]{12}$
                            bankCode:
                              description: SWIFT/BIC code of the bank (e.g.=
 CHASUS33)
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 14
                              pattern: ^[A-Za-z0-9]+$
                              example: CHASUS33
                            bankName:
                              description: Full name of the bank (e.g. The =
Bank of America)
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 105
                              pattern: ^[a-zA-Z0-9\- !,.:\;?_@'()&amp;/ ]*$
                              example: JP Morgan Chase Bank
                            bankLocation:
                              description: City/location of the bank (e.g. =
New York, NY)
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 35
                              pattern: ^[a-zA-Z0-9\- !,.:\;?_@'()&amp;/ ]*$
                              example: New York, NY
                            countryCode:
                              description: &gt;-
                                ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code where the b=
ank
                                is located
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 2
                              pattern: ^[A-Z]{2}$
                              example: US
                          example:
                            id: a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890
                            bankCode: CHASUS33
                            bankName: JP Morgan Chase Bank
                            bankLocation: New York, NY
                            countryCode: US
                      paging:
                        $ref: '#/components/schemas/PagingArray'
                  result:
                    type: object
                    properties:
                      bankDetails:
                        description: &gt;-
                          A list of ids relating to the bank detail records
                          returned
                        type: array
                        items:
                          description: Entity Id
                          type: string
        '400':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/400ErrorResponse'
        '500':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/500ErrorResponse'
  /bankDetailListByNCC:
    get:
      tags:
        - ReferenceData
      description: &gt;-
        Retrieves a list of bank details by NCC (National Clearing Code)
        identifier for a specific country. Searches by partial branch ident=
ifier
        (e.g. ABA for US, CNAPS for CN). Used during international payment
        initiation or beneficiary creation to look up bank details by
        country-specific clearing code. Data is sourced from the bank_list =
table
        filtered by ncc_type matching the country's NCC type from the ncc_r=
ules
        table.
      operationId: getBankDetailListByNCC
      parameters:
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-authorization'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-brandId'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-channelType'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-deviceExperience'
        - name: countryCode
          in: query
          description: ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code to filter banks by (=
e.g. US, CN)
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
            maxLength: 2
            pattern: ^[A-Z]{2}$
          example: US
        - name: nccType
          in: query
          description: &gt;-
            NCC type code identifying the clearing system for the country (=
e.g.
            FW for Fedwire/ABA, CN for CNAPS). Sourced from ncc_rules table=
.
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
            maxLength: 2
            pattern: ^[A-Za-z0-9 ]{1,2}$
          example: FW
        - name: search
          in: query
          description: &gt;-
            Partial NCC/branch identifier code to search for. Minimum 2
            characters. The API will return all banks whose NCC code starts=
 with
            or contains this value.
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
            minLength: 2
            maxLength: 14
            pattern: ^[A-Za-z0-9]+$
          example: '021082'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/pageSize'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/pageKey'
      responses:
        '200':
          description: A list of bank details matching the NCC identifier s=
earch criteria
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
                properties:
                  entities:
                    type: object
                    properties:
                      bankDetails:
                        type: array
                        items:
                          type: object
                          description: &gt;-
                            Bank detail record from bank_list table (NCC
                            entries)
                          required:
                            - id
                            - bankCode
                            - countryCode
                            - nccType
                          properties:
                            id:
                              description: Unique identifier for this bank =
detail record
                              type: string
                              pattern: &gt;-
                                ^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-5][0-9a-f]{3}-[=
089ab][0-9a-f]{3}-[0-9a-f]{12}$
                            nccType:
                              description: NCC type code (e.g. FW for Fedwi=
re/ABA)
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 2
                              pattern: ^[A-Za-z0-9 ]{1,2}$
                              example: FW
                            bankCode:
                              description: &gt;-
                                NCC/branch identifier code (e.g. 021082586 =
for
                                ABA routing number)
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 14
                              pattern: ^[A-Za-z0-9]+$
                              example: '021082586'
                            bankName:
                              description: Full name of the bank
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 105
                              pattern: ^[a-zA-Z0-9\- !,.:\;?_@'()&amp;/ ]*$
                              example: The Bank of America
                            bankLocation:
                              description: City/location of the bank
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 35
                              pattern: ^[a-zA-Z0-9\- !,.:\;?_@'()&amp;/ ]*$
                              example: New York, NY
                            countryCode:
                              description: ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 2
                              pattern: ^[A-Z]{2}$
                              example: US
                          example:
                            id: b2c3d4e5-f6a7-8901-bcde-f12345678901
                            nccType: FW
                            bankCode: '021082586'
                            bankName: The Bank of America
                            bankLocation: New York, NY
                            countryCode: US
                      paging:
                        $ref: '#/components/schemas/PagingArray'
                  result:
                    type: object
                    properties:
                      bankDetails:
                        description: &gt;-
                          A list of ids relating to the bank detail records
                          returned
                        type: array
                        items:
                          description: Entity Id
                          type: string
        '400':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/400ErrorResponse'
        '500':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/500ErrorResponse'
  /countryList:
    get:
      tags:
        - ReferenceData
      description: &gt;-
        Retrieves a list of countries currently supported by W1T for
        international payments and beneficiary creation. Returns country co=
des,
        country names, and the scenario index which determines which combin=
ation
        of fields (IBAN mandatory, NCC mandatory, NCC optional, SWIFT/BIC o=
nly)
        the UI should display for a particular country. Data is sourced fro=
m the
        country_list table, filtered to only include W1T-supported countrie=
s
        (excluding embargoed countries).
      operationId: getCountryList
      parameters:
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-authorization'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-brandId'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-channelType'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-deviceExperience'
      responses:
        '200':
          description: A list of W1T-supported countries with their scenari=
o indicators
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
                properties:
                  entities:
                    type: object
                    properties:
                      countries:
                        type: array
                        items:
                          type: object
                          description: Country reference data from country_=
list table
                          required:
                            - id
                            - countryCode
                            - countryName
                            - scenarioInd
                          properties:
                            id:
                              description: Unique identifier for this count=
ry record
                              type: string
                              pattern: &gt;-
                                ^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-5][0-9a-f]{3}-[=
089ab][0-9a-f]{3}-[0-9a-f]{12}$
                            countryCode:
                              description: &gt;-
                                ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code (e.g. AU, U=
S,
                                GB)
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 2
                              pattern: ^[A-Z]{2}$
                              example: US
                            countryName:
                              description: Full name of the country
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 70
                              pattern: ^[a-zA-Z0-9\- !,.:\;?_@'()&amp;/ ]*$
                              example: United States
                            scenarioInd:
                              description: &gt;-
                                Scenario indicator determining which UI fie=
lds
                                to display. 1=3DIBAN mandatory, 2=3DNCC man=
datory,
                                3=3DNCC optional, 4=3DSWIFT/BIC only
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 1
                              pattern: ^[1-4]$
                              enum:
                                - '1'
                                - '2'
                                - '3'
                                - '4'
                              example: '2'
                          example:
                            id: c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-123456789012
                            countryCode: US
                            countryName: United States
                            scenarioInd: '2'
                  result:
                    type: object
                    properties:
                      countries:
                        description: A list of ids relating to the country =
records returned
                        type: array
                        items:
                          description: Entity Id
                          type: string
        '400':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/400ErrorResponse'
        '500':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/500ErrorResponse'
  /currencyList:
    get:
      tags:
        - ReferenceData
      description: &gt;-
        Retrieves a list of currencies supported for a given country, for u=
ser
        to select when making an international payment or creating an
        international beneficiary. Filtered to only return currencies curre=
ntly
        supported by W1T. Data is sourced by joining the countries_per_curr=
ency
        table (filtered by country code) with the currency_list table to re=
turn
        full currency details.
      operationId: getCurrencyList
      parameters:
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-authorization'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-brandId'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-channelType'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-deviceExperience'
        - name: countryCode
          in: query
          description: &gt;-
            ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code to retrieve supported currencie=
s for
            (e.g. US, GB, JP)
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
            maxLength: 2
            pattern: ^[A-Z]{2}$
          example: US
      responses:
        '200':
          description: A list of W1T-supported currencies for the specified=
 country
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
                properties:
                  entities:
                    type: object
                    properties:
                      currencies:
                        type: array
                        items:
                          type: object
                          description: Currency reference data from currenc=
y_list table
                          required:
                            - id
                            - currencyCode
                            - currencyName
                          properties:
                            id:
                              description: Unique identifier for this curre=
ncy record
                              type: string
                              pattern: &gt;-
                                ^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-5][0-9a-f]{3}-[=
089ab][0-9a-f]{3}-[0-9a-f]{12}$
                            currencyCode:
                              description: &gt;-
                                ISO 4217 three-character currency code (e.g=
.
                                USD, GBP, AUD)
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 3
                              pattern: ^[A-Z]{3}$
                              example: USD
                            currencyName:
                              description: Full name of the currency
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 70
                              pattern: ^[a-zA-Z0-9\- !,.:\;?_@'()&amp;/ ]*$
                              example: US Dollar
                          example:
                            id: d4e5f6a7-b8c9-0123-defa-234567890123
                            currencyCode: USD
                            currencyName: US Dollar
                  result:
                    type: object
                    properties:
                      currencies:
                        description: &gt;-
                          A list of ids relating to the currency records
                          returned
                        type: array
                        items:
                          description: Entity Id
                          type: string
        '400':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/400ErrorResponse'
        '500':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/500ErrorResponse'
  /cutoffList:
    get:
      tags:
        - ReferenceData
      description: &gt;-
        Retrieves the earliest cut-off time for a given country and currenc=
y
        combination to display as a warning to users during payment initiat=
ion.
        The API returns the earliest (minimum) cut-off time by comparing va=
lues
        from the country_cutoff and currency_cutoff tables for the given co=
untry
        code and currency code respectively.
      operationId: getCutoffList
      parameters:
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-authorization'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-brandId'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-channelType'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-deviceExperience'
        - name: countryCode
          in: query
          description: ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code (e.g. US, GB)
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
            maxLength: 2
            pattern: ^[A-Z]{2}$
          example: US
        - name: currencyCode
          in: query
          description: ISO 4217 three-character currency code (e.g. USD, GB=
P)
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
            maxLength: 3
            pattern: ^[A-Z]{3}$
          example: USD
      responses:
        '200':
          description: &gt;-
            The earliest cut-off time for the specified country/currency
            combination
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
                properties:
                  entities:
                    type: object
                    properties:
                      cutoffs:
                        type: array
                        items:
                          type: object
                          description: &gt;-
                            Cut-off time details derived from country_cutof=
f and
                            currency_cutoff tables
                          required:
                            - id
                            - countryCode
                            - currencyCode
                            - cutoffTime
                          properties:
                            id:
                              description: Unique identifier for this cut-o=
ff record
                              type: string
                              pattern: &gt;-
                                ^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-5][0-9a-f]{3}-[=
089ab][0-9a-f]{3}-[0-9a-f]{12}$
                            countryCode:
                              description: ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 2
                              pattern: ^[A-Z]{2}$
                              example: US
                            currencyCode:
                              description: ISO 4217 three-character currenc=
y code
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 3
                              pattern: ^[A-Z]{3}$
                              example: USD
                            cutoffTime:
                              description: &gt;-
                                The earliest cut-off time in HHMM format
                                (24-hour). This is the minimum of the count=
ry
                                cut-off and currency cut-off times.
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 4
                              pattern: ^[0-2][0-9][0-5][0-9]$
                              example: '1430'
                          example:
                            id: e5f6a7b8-c9d0-1234-efab-345678901234
                            countryCode: US
                            currencyCode: USD
                            cutoffTime: '1430'
                  result:
                    type: object
                    properties:
                      cutoffs:
                        description: A list of ids relating to the cut-off =
records returned
                        type: array
                        items:
                          description: Entity Id
                          type: string
        '400':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/400ErrorResponse'
        '500':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/500ErrorResponse'
  /purposeCodeList:
    get:
      tags:
        - ReferenceData
      description: &gt;-
        Retrieves a list of purpose codes and their descriptions for a give=
n
        country, to be displayed in the 'Reason of Payment' dropdown during
        international payment initiation. Purpose codes are country-specifi=
c and
        represent the reason for the international payment (e.g. trade,
        education, medical).
      operationId: getPurposeCodeList
      parameters:
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-authorization'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-brandId'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-channelType'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/x-deviceExperience'
        - name: countryCode
          in: query
          description: &gt;-
            ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code to retrieve purpose codes for (=
e.g.
            IN, CN)
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
            maxLength: 2
            pattern: ^[A-Z]{2}$
          example: IN
      responses:
        '200':
          description: A list of purpose codes for the specified country
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
                properties:
                  entities:
                    type: object
                    properties:
                      purposeCodes:
                        type: array
                        items:
                          type: object
                          description: &gt;-
                            Purpose code entry for the reason of payment
                            dropdown
                          required:
                            - id
                            - purposeCode
                            - description
                          properties:
                            id:
                              description: Unique identifier for this purpo=
se code record
                              type: string
                              pattern: &gt;-
                                ^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-5][0-9a-f]{3}-[=
089ab][0-9a-f]{3}-[0-9a-f]{12}$
                            purposeCode:
                              description: The purpose code value (e.g. P00=
01, TRADE)
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 10
                              pattern: ^[A-Za-z0-9]+$
                              example: P0001
                            description:
                              description: &gt;-
                                Human-readable description of the purpose o=
f
                                payment
                              type: string
                              maxLength: 255
                              pattern: ^[a-zA-Z0-9\- !,.:\;?_@'()&amp;/ ]*$
                              example: Trade - Payment for goods
                          example:
                            id: f6a7b8c9-d0e1-2345-fabc-456789012345
                            purposeCode: P0001
                            description: Trade - Payment for goods
                  result:
                    type: object
                    properties:
                      purposeCodes:
                        description: &gt;-
                          A list of ids relating to the purpose code record=
s
                          returned
                        type: array
                        items:
                          description: Entity Id
                          type: string
        '400':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/400ErrorResponse'
        '500':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/500ErrorResponse'
components:
  securitySchemes:
    BasicAuth:
      type: http
      scheme: basic
    ScopedAccess:
      description: ScopedAccess is used to provide ACL
      type: oauth2
      flows:
        implicit:
          authorizationUrl: https://ignored-for-scoped-access
          scopes: {}
  parameters:
    x-authorization:
      name: x-authorization
      in: header
      description: &gt;-
        The credentials required for authentication or authorisation to a
        downstream system. This header must follow the same conventions as =
for
        the standard HTTP authorization header as defined in RFC2616 (ie. s=
cheme
        and credentials).
      schema:
        type: string
        pattern: ^Bearer\s[\w\.-]+$
    x-brandId:
      name: x-brandId
      in: header
      description: The `brand` as per Enterprise Reference Data
      required: true
      schema:
        type: string
        enum:
          - WBC
          - SGB
          - BSA
          - BOM
          - RAMS
          - WNZL
    x-channelType:
      name: x-channelType
      in: header
      description: Channel Type
      required: true
      schema:
        type: string
        enum:
          - Internal
    x-deviceExperience:
      name: x-deviceExperience
      in: header
      description: &gt;-
        Non-functional header to provide telemetry and debugging aids when
        logged to Splunk.
      schema:
        type: array
        items:
          type: string
          pattern: ^[\w:,-]{1,250}$
      style: simple
      explode: false
      required: true
    pageSize:
      name: pageSize
      in: query
      description: Number of entries to be returned in a single page
      schema:
        type: integer
        format: int32
        minimum: 10
        maximum: 1000
        default: 1000
      required: false
      example: 100
    pageKey:
      name: pageKey
      in: query
      description: The key identifying the page of data to be returned
      schema:
        type: integer
        format: int32
        maximum: 1000
        default: 0
      required: false
  responses:
    400ErrorResponse:
      description: Bad Request
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            type: object
            description: Contains list of Errors
            properties:
              result:
                type: object
                description: Contains list of Errors
                properties:
                  errors:
                    type: array
                    items:
                      type: object
                      description: Represents an individual error
                      properties:
                        code:
                          description: Error Code
                          type: integer
                          format: int32
                          example: 400
                        message:
                          description: Error Message
                          type: string
                          pattern: ^[\w ]+$
                          maxLength: 32
                          example: Bad Request
                        details:
                          description: Detailed information about the error=
.
                          type: string
                          pattern: ^[\w ]+$
                          maxLength: 32
                          example: Check logs for details
                      required:
                        - code
                        - message
    500ErrorResponse:
      description: Internal Server Error
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            type: object
            description: Contains list of Errors
            properties:
              result:
                type: object
                description: Contains list of Errors
                properties:
                  errors:
                    type: array
                    items:
                      type: object
                      description: Represents an individual error
                      properties:
                        code:
                          description: Error Code
                          type: integer
                          format: int32
                          example: 400
                        message:
                          description: Error Message
                          type: string
                          pattern: ^[\w ]+$
                          maxLength: 32
                          example: Bad Request
                        details:
                          description: Detailed information about the error=
.
                          type: string
                          pattern: ^[\w ]+$
                          maxLength: 32
                          example: Check logs for details
                      required:
                        - code
                        - message
  schemas:
    PagingArray:
      type: array
      items:
        type: object
        properties:
          id:
            description: Paging Unique Id
            type: string
            maxLength: 3
            pattern: ^\d+$
            example: '1'
          pageSize:
            description: Number of items per page
            type: integer
            format: int32
            example: 50
          count:
            description: Total number of items available
            type: integer
            format: int32
            example: 160
          previousPageKey:
            description: Key for start of previous page
            type: string
            pattern: ^\d+$
            maxLength: 3
            example: '0'
          nextPageKey:
            description: Key for start of next page
            type: string
            pattern: ^\d+$
            maxLength: 3
            example: '2'
          moreItems:
            description: Indicator to show if there are more items availabl=
e
            type: boolean
            example: true

</pre>
